 function and meaning of tree art, its role within First Nations cosmology, and the need for greater respect for all of our natural resources. This fascinating study of a haunting and little-known cultural phenomenon helps us to see our forests with new eyes.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aNATURE / Plants / Trees.2bisacsh1 aJensen, Doreen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMills, Antonia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077356960740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773569607423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773569607/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles